wthymo7WVLsgoRTcxVXdfronfYrkU9fqz_fgSP5whBmw3czQVvvBepcYYAueZwo8YKlXEmXy8hu=
BA3hwqu41R2L9qT6uxiVYV_01-hhZcy] at a $5.6 billion valuation. More than 3x =
growth in valuation in eight months implies that options trading was workin=
g well for the company, but it also introduced a whole new level of risk, f=
or users and for the company itself.
Between the Series C in 2017 and the beginning of 2020, Robinhood grew stea=
dily from 2 million to 10 million users. Then COVID hit, and things started=
